# Committed test fixtures are byte-exact and verified across languages and OSes:
#
#   * opengeni-agent-update/tests/fixtures — signed release artifacts whose bytes
#     are checked by the update flow's sha256 checksum gate AND its minisign
#     signature gate (flow.rs). A single changed byte fails both gates.
#   * opengeni-relay/tests/fixtures, agent-proto cross-stack fixtures — TS↔Rust
#     token / encoding parity vectors compared byte-for-byte.
#
# Git's automatic CRLF translation (the GitHub-hosted Windows runner ships
# core.autocrlf=true) rewrites the line endings of these LF text files on
# checkout, changing their bytes and breaking the byte-exact checks — which is
# exactly what failed the windows-latest Agent CI leg. Treat every committed
# fixture as binary so the working tree is identical on every OS.
**/tests/fixtures/** -text
